App Flow Documentation

1. After website loads , the user clicks on google login button. (if network is slow please wait untill the google script loads)

2. It will open a popup for google signin and it requests access for google drive metadata

3. After we got the access, the access_token will be saved in the vuex store(state management in vue)

4. access_token will be send to the backend for getting google drive files (first 10 files)

5. files will be displayed in table

6. view_more button will get another 10 files from the google drive

Running the app locally

1. Clone the project

2. npm i  -  installs the required dependencies

3. npm run serve  -  starts the project locally

Note: Ensure port 8080 is not used by any other application
